TEKsystems Global Services is seeking Data Annotators and Data Labeling specialists to support our AI and machine learning teams in developing and optimizing Artificial Intelligence solutions.
Responsibilities For Data Annotators:
* Annotate large datasets with accurate labels that will be used to train and validate AI models.
* Review data inputs and outputs to ensure consistency and quality of annotations.
* Use annotation tools to mark up text, images, or other data according to specific guidelines.
Preferred Qualifications For Data Annotators:
* Experience in data annotation or a related field.
* Familiarity with AI and machine learning concepts.
* Native Speaker in one of the following languages: Spanish, Portuguese, or Hindi
Responsibilities For Prompt Engineers:
* You'll work closely with Eng and Prod team to understand their questions and needs, and then work on how we can optimize a solution based on prompt creation and engineering methods
* You'll develop and write prompts, build characters (e.g, Character.ai (, and use the right combination of tools and frameworks to evaluate your prompts and models
Bachelor's degree in Media Studies, Communications, Psychology, Law, or related field preferred.
Prior experience in content moderation, data annotation, or policy enforcement roles.

This is a Contract position based out of Dallas, TX.

The pay range for this position is $20.00 - $20.00/hr.
Eligibility requirements apply to some benefits and may depend on your job classification and length of employment. Benefits are subject to change and may be subject to specific elections, plan, or program terms. If eligible, the benefits available for this temporary role may include the following: Medical, dental & vision Critical Illness, Accident, and Hospital 401(k) Retirement Plan - Pre-tax and Roth post-tax contributions available Life Insurance (Voluntary Life & AD&D for the employee and dependents) Short and long-term disability Health Spending Account (HSA) Transportation benefits Employee Assistance Program Time Off/Leave (PTO, Vacation or Sick Leave)

This is a fully remote position.

This position is anticipated to close on Jan 16, 2026.
